## 5. Layer Adherence Summary

| Component | Layer | Rationale |
|-----------|-------|-----------|
| `IActionSyncStrategy` | Application | Defines the contract; no external dependencies |
| `IActionSyncStrategyFactory` | Application | Factory interface for strategy selection |
| `GameMode` enum | Core/Domain | Domain concept affecting business rules |
| `Player.GameMode` property | Core/Domain | Domain state on the aggregate |
| `OfflineQueuingStrategy` | Infrastructure | Uses SQLite repository (Infrastructure concern) |
| `RealTimeSyncStrategy` | Infrastructure | Uses `IApiClient` for HTTP calls |
| `ActionSyncStrategyFactory` | Infrastructure | Concrete implementation with external dependencies |

This placement follows the **Dependency Inversion Principle** established in ADR-001: interfaces are defined in the Application layer, implementations live in Infrastructure, and the Domain layer remains pure C# with no external dependencies.

